- 'NFC West' is one of the conferences in the NFL (National Football League).;
- 'Most successful' is inferred based on higher win percentages. Teams with higher win percentages are considered more successful.;

- 'Sailed smoothly through the turbulent seas' is a metaphor for achieving a win percentage over 50%.;
- 'In the shadows of their peers in terms of raw performance' refers to having a raw rank lower than the average raw rank across all teams.;
- 'Unexpected voyagers' metaphorically represents teams that outperform in wins but underperform in raw metrics.;

- Successful teams are those who are performing well above average.; 
- In this context, 'doing better than average' means having a win percentage greater than 50%.;
- The AFC refers to the American Football Conference.; 
- Teams are considered part of the AFC if they belong to a division within the AFC.

